# Email Marketing Module Rules

- Read `contracts.ts` before changing the module.
- Import all domain DTOs from `contracts.ts`; do not use `@/types/api`.
- Use `ENDPOINTS` and `ROUTES`; never hardcode API paths in pages or services.
- The service accepts governed v2 envelopes only and must preserve correlation,
  timestamp, and pagination metadata.
- Lifecycle state, counters, provider evidence, tenant ownership, and audit fields
  are server-controlled and never writable from forms.
- Queue acceptance is not delivery success. UI copy must preserve that boundary.
- Consent and suppression records are append-only or lifecycle-controlled; do not
  add edit pages.
- Routes belong in `routes.ts`; do not add static sidebar entries.
- Run the module typecheck, zero-warning lint, and tests after every change.
